#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Āhāravagga "
msgstr "2. Fuel "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Paccayasutta "
msgstr "20. Conditions "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn12.20:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:1.2"
msgid "“Paṭiccasamuppādañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi paṭiccasamuppanne ca dhamme. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you dependent origination and dependently originated phenomena. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:1.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.20:2.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo? "
msgstr "“And what is dependent origination? "

msgctxt "sn12.20:2.2"
msgid "Jātipaccayā, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death. "

# NOTE: Note That BB’s note here says that the identical passage is found at AN 3.136, but there idapaccayata is omitted.
msgctxt "sn12.20:2.3"
msgid "Uppādā vā tathāgatānaṃ anuppādā vā tathāgatānaṃ, ṭhitāva sā dhātu dhammaṭṭhitatā dhammaniyāmatā idappaccayatā. "
msgstr "Whether Realized Ones arise or not, this law of nature persists, this regularity of natural principles, this invariance of natural principles, specific conditionality. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:2.4"
msgid "Taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti. "
msgstr "A Realized One understands this and comprehends it, "

msgctxt "sn12.20:2.5"
msgid "Abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā ācikkhati deseti paññāpeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti. "
msgstr "then he explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals it. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:2.6"
msgid "‘Passathā’ti cāha: "
msgstr "‘Look,’ he says, "

msgctxt "sn12.20:2.7"
msgid "‘jātipaccayā, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇaṃ’. "
msgstr "‘Rebirth is a condition for old age and death.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.26, sc3
msgctxt "sn12.20:3.1"
msgid "Bhavapaccayā, bhikkhave, jāti … pe … "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.2"
msgid "upādānapaccayā, bhikkhave, bhavo … "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.3"
msgid "taṇhāpaccayā, bhikkhave, upādānaṃ … "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:3.4"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā, bhikkhave, taṇhā … "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.5"
msgid "phassapaccayā, bhikkhave, vedanā … "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.6"
msgid "saḷāyatanapaccayā, bhikkhave, phasso … "
msgstr "The six sense fields are a condition for contact … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.7"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā, bhikkhave, saḷāyatanaṃ … "
msgstr "Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:3.8"
msgid "viññāṇapaccayā, bhikkhave, nāmarūpaṃ … "
msgstr "Consciousness is a condition for name and form … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:3.9"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "Choices are a condition for consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.10"
msgid "avijjāpaccayā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā "
msgstr "Ignorance is a condition for choices. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.11"
msgid "uppādā vā tathāgatānaṃ anuppādā vā tathāgatānaṃ, ṭhitāva sā dhātu dhammaṭṭhitatā dhammaniyāmatā idappaccayatā. "
msgstr "Whether Realized Ones arise or not, this law of nature persists, this regularity of natural principles, this invariance of natural principles, specific conditionality. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.12"
msgid "Taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti. "
msgstr "A Realized One understands this and comprehends it, "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.13"
msgid "Abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā ācikkhati deseti paññāpeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti. "
msgstr "then he explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals it. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.14"
msgid "‘Passathā’ti cāha: "
msgstr "‘Look,’ he says, "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.15"
msgid "‘avijjāpaccayā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā’. "
msgstr "‘Ignorance is a condition for choices.’ "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.16"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, yā tatra tathatā avitathatā anaññathatā idappaccayatā—"
msgstr "So the fact that this is real, not unreal, not otherwise; the specific conditionality of it: "

msgctxt "sn12.20:3.17"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo. "
msgstr "this is called dependent origination. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn12.20:4.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppannā dhammā? "
msgstr "And what are the dependently originated phenomena? "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.2"
msgid "Jarāmaraṇaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ saṅkhataṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ khayadhammaṃ vayadhammaṃ virāgadhammaṃ nirodhadhammaṃ. "
msgstr "Old age and death are impermanent, conditioned, dependently originated, liable to end, vanish, fade away, and cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.3"
msgid "Jāti, bhikkhave, aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā khayadhammā vayadhammā virāgadhammā nirodhadhammā. "
msgstr "Rebirth … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.4"
msgid "Bhavo, bhikkhave, anicco saṅkhato paṭiccasamuppanno khayadhammo vayadhammo virāgadhammo nirodhadhammo. "
msgstr "Continued existence … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.5"
msgid "Upādānaṃ bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "Grasping … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.6"
msgid "taṇhā, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Craving … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:4.7"
msgid "vedanā, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Feeling … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.8"
msgid "phasso, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Contact … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.9"
msgid "saḷāyatanaṃ, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "The six sense fields … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.10"
msgid "nāmarūpaṃ, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Name and form … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:4.11"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Consciousness … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.20:4.12"
msgid "saṅkhārā, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Choices … "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.13"
msgid "avijjā, bhikkhave, aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā khayadhammā vayadhammā virāgadhammā nirodhadhammā. "
msgstr "Ignorance is impermanent, conditioned, dependently originated, liable to end, vanish, fade away, and cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.20:4.14"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppannā dhammā. "
msgstr "These are called the dependently originated phenomena. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.27, sc5
#. VAR: paṭidhāvissati → paridhāvissati (bj)
msgctxt "sn12.20:5.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa ‘ayañca paṭiccasamuppādo, ime ca paṭiccasamuppannā dhammā’ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti, so vata pubbantaṃ vā paṭidhāvissati: "
msgstr "When a noble disciple has clearly seen with right wisdom this dependent origination and these dependently originated phenomena as they are, it’s impossible for them to turn back to the past, thinking: "

#. VAR: ahosiṃ nu kho ahaṃ → nu khvāhaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.20:5.2"
msgid "‘ahosiṃ nu kho ahaṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, nanu kho ahosiṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ nu kho ahosiṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, kathaṃ nu kho ahosiṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ hutvā kiṃ ahosiṃ nu kho ahaṃ atītamaddhānan’ti; "
msgstr "‘Did I exist in the past? Did I not exist in the past? What was I in the past? How was I in the past? After being what, what did I become in the past?’ "

#. VAR: upadhāvissati → apadhāvissati (mr)
msgctxt "sn12.20:5.3"
msgid "aparantaṃ vā upadhāvissati: "
msgstr "Or to turn forward to the future, thinking: "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.4"
msgid "‘bhavissāmi nu kho ahaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, nanu kho bhavissāmi anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ nu kho bhavissāmi anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kathaṃ nu kho bhavissāmi anāgatamaddhānaṃ, kiṃ hutvā kiṃ bhavissāmi nu kho ahaṃ anāgatamaddhānan’ti; "
msgstr "‘Will I exist in the future? Will I not exist in the future? What will I be in the future? How will I be in the future? After being what, what will I become in the future?’ "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.5"
msgid "etarahi vā paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ ajjhattaṃ kathaṃkathī bhavissati: "
msgstr "Or to be undecided about the present, thinking: "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.6"
msgid "‘ahaṃ nu khosmi, no nu khosmi, kiṃ nu khosmi, kathaṃ nu khosmi, ayaṃ nu kho satto kuto āgato, so kuhiṃ gamissatī’ti—"
msgstr "‘Am I? Am I not? What am I? How am I? This sentient being—where did it come from? And where will it go?’ "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.7"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn12.20:5.9"
msgid "Tathā hi, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa ayañca paṭiccasamuppādo ime ca paṭiccasamuppannā dhammā yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā”ti. "
msgstr "Because that noble disciple has clearly seen with right wisdom this dependent origination and these dependently originated phenomena as they are.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.20:5.10"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.20:5.11"
msgid "Āhāravaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.1"
msgid "Āhāraṃ phagguno ceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.2"
msgid "Dve ca samaṇabrāhmaṇā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.3"
msgid "Kaccānagotta dhammakathikaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.4"
msgid "Acelaṃ timbarukena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.5"
msgid "Bālapaṇḍitato ceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.20:6.6"
msgid "Dasamo paccayena cāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
